cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.CY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language): The study examines language variation on Twitter in discourse related to the 2017 independence referendum in Catalonia, which falls under the scope of computational linguistics. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The study analyzes social media data to investigate the relationship between political identity and language variation, which falls under the scope of social and information networks. 
- cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing): Although not the main focus of the study, the use of language on social media can be considered a form of sound and music computing, as it involves the analysis of acoustic signals (i.e., written language). 
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science): The study applies computational methods to investigate a social phenomenon (i.e., political identity and language variation) on social media, which falls under the scope of computational social science. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The study touches upon the sociocultural aspect of language use in the context of political identity, which falls under the scope of computers and society.
